/MATE contains my original files for the MATE technique of power system simulation.
MATE is explained in the UBC paper by Marti et al.

The MATE algorith is not used a lot but the folder contains many useful routines.
/net contains routines to get the Native Simscape Electrical netlist
/m also, including single-phase diagram but I find that /net works better.

To Mathworks people: why not release the code to get this netlist, that would be fun and would avoid me week-ends to figure out fancy bugs in my code!
